data.title: An interview with Atticus' Nathan Phelps
data.meta_description: Nathan Phelps is part of the passionate team making Atticus the #1 probate, estate settlement and inheritance software for helping families simplify and navigate life after the loss of a loved one. Download our 5 star mobile app or create an account online to get started and learn more today.
data.text:
Tell us about yourself:

Nathan was born in Boston and is now based in Nashville, TN with a Bachelors in Business Administration. Nathans writing and marketing chops have been seen by well a lot of people in a lot of different places! SaaS, organic food, a world famous piano and cello duo, fancy bamboo toilet paper!?

If it has a good mission and good people behind it, Nathan is down to talk about it (maybe more than he should).



Why did you join Atticus?

He joined Atticus because Ben was cool. Okay  maybe a little more than that. He thinks what the team is building is incredibly helpful to people and worth having in the world, and thats reason enough for him.



Fun fact?

I once woke up at a festival after napping in our band van, stepped out into the bright sunlight of the artist parking lot, and almost stumbled straight into Tim McGraw shirtless pulling a weight sled.
